Marketing Manager - Female
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 16:04:55
Ref. JB3047523
Job Description
A marketing manager is a person who is involved in developing marketing campaigns that promote a product, service or idea.
She plans, advertises and organises public relations, events, develop product campaigns, their distribution, sponsorships and conduct research.
Tasks will involve:
Maintaining, updating and developing the website
Managing social media and social media advertising
Sending quotations and portfolios out to clients
Writing and distributing press releases
Arranging and supervise photoshoots when necessary
Maintaining and updating customer databases
Managing client relationship
Communicating with target audiences and managing customer relationships
Sourcing advertising opportunities and placing adverts in the press - local, regional, national and specialist publications - or on the radio, depending on the organisation and the campaign
Managing the production of marketing materials, including leaflets, posters, flyers, newsletters, and e-newsletters
Writing and proofreading copy
Liaising with designers and printers
Arranging the effective distribution of marketing materials
Organising and attending events such as conferences, seminars, Receptions and exhibitions
Sourcing and securing sponsorship
Conducting market research, for example using customer Questionnaires and focus groups
Contributing to, and developing, marketing plans and strategies
Managing budgets
Evaluating marketing campaigns
Monitoring competitor activity
Skills
Sales Skills
Social Media Skills
E-Marketing Skills are crucial
Data/ Analytics Skills
Collaboration AND exceptional communication
Creativity/Innovation
Understanding technology
Writing skills are critical
Influencing and negotiation skills
Drive and ambition
This job is posted in the following Specialties:
Education
Bachelor degree
